english:
  title: In Praise of the Marquis of Shouchun
  author: Lee Gyeong-bo
  language: eng
  text: It is natural that the bonds of blood kindle the deepest affection. Thus, since ancient times, when rulers have exercised their sovereign power to enfeoff their sons and brothers, even those still nursing at their mother's breast have worn great seals at their waists and attended court—such is the proper order of things. How much more so for one advanced in years and rich in virtue, who stands as an exemplar among the royal kinfolk, whose luminous ribbons and gleaming tablets have long adorned him with princely rank? Should he not now be granted dominion over a fair domain, that such extraordinary favor be made manifest?
